                    </div>
                    <span>While this book does cover the software mentioned in its title, it spends a lot of time with the Apache 1.3 series. In fact, Apache 2.0 was still in beta when the book was published so the author seems a little apprehensive with the material.<P>It is nice as a general overview, and contains a lot of good "filler" such as an appendix on common Unix commands and Unix text editors.<P></span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">very badly written and badly organized</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
